<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/111:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-15">September 15, 1919</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                September 15—11:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>69A [<hi rend="italic">69</hi>]. The following telegram has just been
                            received with request that it be forwarded.</p>
                        <pb facs="0730" n="680" xml:id="pg_680"/>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“President Supreme Council, Peace Conference, Paris. The Hungarian
                                Government, in view of the imminent danger which threatens the
                                country on account of Roumania, desires to be placed under the
                                protection of the Supreme Council of Versailles and requests the
                                Supreme Council to make decision to this end as soon as possible.
                                Friedrich MP, President of the Council.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>